          "description": "This review is in reference to Dr. Stephen Dunay who was condescending, unhelpful and defensive with his macho arms crossed when conversing with me. He said Lenox Hill probably accounts me as a \"problematic\" patient. He didn't want to understand why I didn't want to receive care there. He was mean, uncooperative and a walking ego. He also offered to do a major procedure there until I questioned it since another physician told me that it's unavailable in the ER. His response after his nurse validated the other doctor was, \"well I am here only two days out of the week, so uh huh huh\" (dumb laughter). The images attached are where this ER is sending patients and demonstrates where this Dunay doctor thought I should have stayed. Dangerous Dunay. He is bad bad bad. I accepted that he wouldn't assist me with a recommendation elsewhere, mentioning that he had been condescending towards me. His response was, an automatic rapid one with, \"no, I wasn't, no, I wasn't.\" Almost akin to a bratty child who should not be seeing patients. Everyone else was lovely during my prior visits.",
