        {
          "username": "Soraya Jamie Montalvo",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "104600707063332633219",
          "user_review_count": 104,
          "user_photo_count": 100,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwqy9somege1efUQvwoKNj07xO46YN14g9W25VMWJzvd-YwbzT=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "Came in today, close to 10 am. The security guard asked why I was there.  I stated I needed emergency care. What a question?!! A negative attitude followed. He was intrusive and hostile as he asked to check my bag. He was rude and intimidating.  I told him so and instead of listening and easying up, he responded with additional attitude. In some points of check in with this security guard, his hostility was alarming, where I felt physically unsafe.\nDeciding to make the call of going to the emergency room is hard enough, being greeted with overbearing security guards is not necessary.\nUpon entering,  the technician had a problem with the EKG machine. She appeared already flustered,  frustrated by intake procedures.\nI made the call to refuse further examination.\nMy primary care doctor was able to see me later today.\nThis treatment by security is not uncommon here for me. It's happened before where I have walked out without being seen by the emergency room staff.\nThe entrance on 13th street by security in that entrance has also been pushy and rude in checking bags. I do believe there could be a level of racial profiling.\nEither way, I will seek an alternative to emergency room options. I regret the billing to my insurance from this.\n\nUpdate May 20, 2026\n\nDear Northwell Health Patient Relations Team,\n\nI am writing to share feedback regarding my recent visit to the Greenwich Emergency Room. I arrived at approximately 7:15 PM following concerns that I was experiencing a second TIA.\n\nI would like to begin by noting that I was pleased to find the security check-in process was not invasive, which is a significant improvement over my previous experiences that I had reported to Northwell. While the intake process could still be more user-friendly, I was very impressed by the medical response. Due to the nature of my symptoms, I was quickly taken for a CT scan.\n\nI want to specifically commend the technicians, Troy and Shaka. They were incredibly reassuring and professional during a stressful time. Additionally, the EKG and chest X-ray processes were handled efficiently, and the doctors were very thorough.\n\nRegarding my discharge, the medical team recommended a transfer to Lenox Hill for an MRI. Unfortunately, after waiting five hours for transport, I felt I could no longer stay. I was in significant discomfort from the IV and decided to be discharged against medical advice. While the doctor kindly tried to encourage me to stay, I did not feel I could endure further waiting at that time. I have since consulted with my primary care physician and completed the MRI the next day at Lenox Hill.\n\nOverall, my experience at Greenwich ER was a positive one. I particularly want to mention that the second doctor who treated me was exceptionally caring and clear. Despite the long wait for the transfer, I felt the staff did their best to provide high-quality care.\n\nBest regards,\n\nSoraya Jamie Montalvo",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21ZeWFUaDJXbkZDZG1GWWJFdHhhVmczTXpKc1MwRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x5efa7abe8c75519e!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOmYyaTh2WnFCdmFYbEtxaVg3MzJsS0E%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "Edited a month ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-05-20T17:43:40+00:00"
        },
