          "description": "AVOID AT ALL COSTS. $4k for a glucose monitor and 2 antacids and the audacity to kick someone out  after scolding them immediately after they become conscious clearly because the patient doesn't have insurance(Dr. Max Lazarus will be reported to the New York State medical board). Can't recommend that you avoid this place enough. You're better off contacting a witch doctor  for actual lifesaving care and you'll definitely pay less. They closed ethics claims without so much as an email or phone call response and should not be trusted with anyone's life based on their treatment in what I witnessed.",
